sentences: Ledford grew up in Detroit and attended Berklee College of Music between 1978 and 1982.
In 1986, he began a working relationship with Pat Metheny, appearing live with the Pat Metheny Group and on recordings, such as Secret Story and Still Life (Talking).
Between 1990 and 1992, Ledford taught master classes in trumpet at the Banff Centre in Alberta, Canada.
In 1998, he released a solo album, Miles 2 Go, a tribute to Miles Davis.
On November 1, 2004, Ledford died of heart disease in Los Angeles.

sentences: Mark Ledford (1960 – November 1, 2004) was an American trumpeter, singer, and guitarist.
He would also later contribute to the soundtracks for the Spike Lee films Mo' Better Blues and Do the Right Thing.
